[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "64c7b2196464306c5fabad1453f15cc7ba6d922e930474158a68b0656bacfaf6"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/blackwood"]
[Student "S"]
{You have a good hand, but not good enough to jump-shift at your first turn. So you respond 1\S. Partner now jumps to 3\S.  

Partner has 16-18 points and \S support. It depends on the Aces so you bid 4NT. His answer is 5\H.  

You are missing one Ace but 6\S should be a good slam.}

